    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-27T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-27T18:00:00-05:00" n="524"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d524">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.CC/12–2744: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Donnelly</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-27T20:00:00-03:00"
                            >December 27, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4546. Department’s 3733, December 18, 7 p.m., and Embassy’s 3754, October 18, 6
                        p.m.<note n="79" xml:id="d524fn79">Latter not printed.</note> Velloso<note
                        n="80" xml:id="d524fn80">Pedro Leão Velloso, Acting Foreign Minister of
                        Brazil.</note> said to me today that the Brazilian <pb facs="0967" n="953"
                        xml:id="pg_953"/> Government obviously prefers and considers that it is
                    entitled to a permanent seat on the Security Council but if it cannot be
                    arranged that Brazil should receive one of the first non-permanent seats. I
                    believe that Brazil would be satisfied with the latter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Donnelly</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
